On 28-Mar-04, at 3:41 PM, Doktor Tim wrote:

> At 11:37 AM 03/28/2004, you wrote:
>
>> QUESTION: How do I make the tool required to get the plastic ignition 
>> housing apart?? I seem to remember reading a description of this 
>> process recently but now that I actually need the info I can't 
>> remember where I saw it. I did check the type2 library, but there is 
>> nothing there to help with the late-bay ignition housing.
>
> Did you say you have the Bentley?? Remove the steering wheel and upper 
> switches. Remove lock bolt for housing clamp. Turn key to unlock 
> column and pull the housing off. Find tiny screw that holds the 
> electrical portion of the switch. R&R switch. You don't need to remove 
> the key cylinder housing unless the tab is broken or it is worn badly.
